# research_notebook/ — personal sandbox + GIGANTIC's own AI infrastructure sandbox.
# Per gigantic_project-COPYME/ai/ai_FYIs/gigantic_conventions.md §1, §9, §25, §59.
#
# What ships:
#   - This .gitignore
#   - README.md at any depth in research_ai/ (project-wide doc-ships
#     convention). Inside research_user/, README is suppressed by
#     default so user prose stays local.
#   - .gitkeep at any depth (preserves per-subproject directory
#     structure for git in both research_ai/ and research_user/)
#   - GIGANTIC toolkits (per §59) ship from research_ai/subproject-<X>/.
#     research_ai/ default-ships so toolkits track without any explicit
#     carve-out — they just live there and are tracked normally.
#
# What does NOT ship:
#   - research_user/** — personal sandbox; ships ONLY the
#     per-subproject .gitkeep placeholders.
#   - research_ai/sessions/*.jsonl.gz — captured session transcripts
#     (gitignored by the catch-all below; never edited / deleted)
#   - research_ai/sessions/TRANSCRIPT_CAPTURE_LOG.md — per-project local
#     capture log (also caught by the catch-all)
#   - Any other personal content (notes, draft analyses, downloaded data)

# Default: ignore everything in this tree
*

# Allow traversal into subdirectories (so the rules below can match)
!*/

# Keep this .gitignore
!.gitignore

# Keep README.md at any depth (project-wide doc-ships convention)
!README.md

# Keep .gitkeep stubs at any depth (preserves per-subproject directory
# structure for git, including subproject-<X>/.gitkeep placeholders)
!.gitkeep
!**/.gitkeep

# §59 toolkits: re-include the entire toolkit subtree under
# research_ai/subproject-<X>/. Toolkits ship full content (scripts,
# configs, main.nf, AI_GUIDEs, INPUT_user template, etc.) — same
# rigor as a subproject workflow. x_* archives inside still get
# ignored by the x_* rule at the bottom of this file.
!research_ai/subproject-*/**

# Re-exclude RUN execution artifacts under research_ai/ toolkits. The broad
# re-inclusion above otherwise tracks NextFlow caches + RUN outputs (e.g. a
# 100MB toolkit-RUN_*/ tree). The top-level .gitignore's RUN-artifact rules do
# NOT reach here — this nested .gitignore takes precedence for this subtree, so
# the carve-outs must live here. Toolkit/workflow SOURCE (COPYME templates,
# scripts, docs) stays tracked; execution copies + their outputs/caches do not.
research_ai/subproject-*/**/work/
research_ai/subproject-*/**/.nextflow/
research_ai/subproject-*/**/.nextflow.log*
research_ai/subproject-*/**/.params.json
research_ai/subproject-*/**/slurm_logs/
research_ai/subproject-*/**/OUTPUT_pipeline/
research_ai/subproject-*/**/toolkit-RUN_*/
research_ai/subproject-*/**/workflow-RUN_*/

# research_user/ is a personal sandbox per §25 — by default ships ONLY
# the per-subproject .gitkeep placeholders so users have pre-materialized
# subproject-<X>/ directories. README.md is suppressed inside
# research_user/ so user prose stays local.
research_user/**
# Re-include subproject-* directories so git can descend into them.
# Per git docs: "It is not possible to re-include a file if a parent
# directory of that file is excluded." So we must un-ignore the dirs
# (trailing slash = directory match) BEFORE re-including files inside.
!research_user/subproject-*/
!research_user/subproject-*/**/
# Allow the per-subproject .gitkeep placeholders at any depth
!research_user/.gitkeep
!research_user/**/.gitkeep
# (Toolkits no longer live here per §59 — they live in research_ai/.
# See git history commit 5cb8e3f for the prior toolkit location.)

# Archive directories: anything starting with x_ is a disposable archive
# and must stay ignored even if it contains files that would otherwise
# be tracked (including x_* backups inside a toolkit). Place AFTER all
# exceptions so this rule wins for x_-prefixed paths.
x_*
**/x_*
